# Varys Deploy & Commit Checklist

After any frontend change (TypeScript / CSS / assets), always run `bash deploy.sh`
then commit **all** of the following files together — never commit a subset:

```
src/                                   # TypeScript source
style/                                 # CSS
lib/                                   # compiled JS output (npx tsc)
varys/labextension/static/             # webpack bundle (remoteEntry + chunks)
varys/labextension/package.json        # ← CRITICAL: points to the active remoteEntry hash
```

## Why `varys/labextension/package.json` matters

JupyterLab reads this file to discover which webpack bundle to load.
If it is stale (points to an old `remoteEntry*.js` hash), `pip install --force-reinstall`
on other machines will install the new bundle files but load the wrong one — the old UI.

## Verification step (always do this before answering "yes, I pushed")

```bash
# Hash in repo must match the file that exists in static/
git show HEAD:varys/labextension/package.json \
  | python3 -c "import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); \
    print(d.get('jupyterlab',{}).get('_build',{}).get('load','N/A'))"

ls varys/labextension/static/remoteEntry*.js
```

Both must show the **same hash**. If they differ, stage and commit `varys/labextension/package.json`.

## Backend-only changes (Python)

No build needed. Just commit the `.py` files and push.
